Capstone Project - Paper Consumption Survey

Author
Affiliation

Ella Haechler

ETH Zurich

Published

May 27, 2025

Abstract
This survey is about the research question on how the consumption of paper changes between Bachelor and Master students at ETH.

Introduction

In recent years, sustainability and resource management have gained importance. Large institutions, including universities, are seeking ways to contribute to a more environmentally friendly future and are actively pursuing new strategies for improvement (âPreferring Print,â 2023). Among the various challenges they face, paper consumption stands out as an area with considerable potential for positive change.

An anonymous survey examined the paper usage habits of ETH students. The studyâs goal was to investigate the differences in paper consumption between bachelor and master students at ETH. The analysis of these usage patterns will help to develop future strategies that promote a more responsible use of resources at universities.

Methods

Data for this study was collected through a survey designed using Google Forms, comprising fifteen questions focused on paper consumption habits. The target population included students currently enrolled in bachelorâs or masterâs programs at ETH Zurich. The survey link was distributed to fellow students via WhatsApp. Additional participants were recruited in person by approaching students on campus. In total, thirty responses were gathered for analysis. This approach ensured a mix of convenience and random sampling within the ETH student community.
